<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1754,1959]" pageId="2" pageNumber="353">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1898,1923]" pageId="2" pageNumber="353">Distribution.</emphasis>
From central 
<collectingCountry box="[533,578,1899,1922]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="353">Iran</collectingCountry>
over southern 
<collectingCountry box="[768,923,1898,1923]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="353">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
eastwards to eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1193,1322,1898,1923]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="353">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
, northern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,288,1934,1959]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="353">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
and western 
<collectingCountry box="[436,531,1934,1959]" name="Pakistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="353">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[546,615,1934,1959]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="4.[151,250,945,967]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,923]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,923]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 9. Distribution of the six Haetosmia species. Green squares = H. circumventa; blue circles = H.ethiopiensis; orange circles = H.vechti; red triangles = H. altera; blue diamonds = H. brachyura; light blue square = H. pakistaniensis. Made with Natural Earth (www.naturalearthdata.com)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1068116/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="353">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1068114/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" targetBox="[174,1409,217,1790]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1827,2033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,317,1827,1850]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">FIGURES 1–8.</emphasis>
Biology of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Peters" authorityYear="1974" box="[449,559,1828,1849]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[449,559,1828,1849]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Haetosmia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 1: Sandy habitat of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[787,945,1828,1849]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="circumventa">
<emphasis box="[787,945,1828,1849]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">H. circumventa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in southwestern Morocco 30 km NE Sidi Ifni (Photo V. Mauss). 2: 
<taxonomicName box="[365,501,1858,1880]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Heliotropium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[365,501,1858,1880]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Heliotropium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[513,656,1858,1880]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Boraginaceae</taxonomicName>
), the exclusive pollen host of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Peters" authorityYear="1974" box="[958,1068,1859,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[958,1068,1859,1880]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Haetosmia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Photo M. Modzelevich). 3: Female proboscis of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[291,387,1889,1911]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Heliotropium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vechti">
<emphasis box="[291,387,1889,1911]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">H. vechti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with specialized pollen-harvesting bristles on the second segment of both labial palpi. 4: Pollenharvesting bristles. 5: Female of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[498,656,1921,1942]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="circumventa">
<emphasis box="[498,656,1921,1942]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">H. circumventa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collecting pollen on 
<taxonomicName box="[883,1019,1919,1941]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Heliotropium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[883,1019,1919,1941]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Heliotropium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Photo C. Sedivy). 6: Female tibia and basitarsus of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[287,379,1950,1972]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Heliotropium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vechti">
<emphasis box="[287,379,1950,1972]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">H. vechti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with specialized long bristles possibly used for nest excavation. 7: Female of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[1185,1277,1950,1972]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Heliotropium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vechti">
<emphasis box="[1185,1277,1950,1972]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">H. vechti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
harvesting leaf pulp on 
<taxonomicName box="[235,458,1982,2003]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procurrens">
<emphasis box="[235,458,1982,2003]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Centaurea procurrens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Photo G. Pisanty). 8: Cluster of six brood cells of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[980,1072,1981,2003]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Heliotropium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vechti">
<emphasis box="[980,1072,1981,2003]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">H. vechti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in excavated chamber in sandy soil (Photo G. Pisanty).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1068116/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" targetBox="[151,1436,193,923]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,945,1028]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,945,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">FIGURE 9.</emphasis>
Distribution of the six 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Peters" authorityYear="1974" box="[513,623,946,967]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[513,623,946,967]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">Haetosmia</emphasis>
