<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1072,1422]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,348,1072,1097]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">Pollen hosts.</emphasis>
All six pollen loads (from three different localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[949,997,1073,1096]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1007,1144,1072,1097]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1198,1295,1072,1097]" name="Pakistan" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
) exclusively consisted of pollen of 
<taxonomicName box="[416,565,1108,1133]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Heliotropium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[416,565,1108,1133]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">Heliotropium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, suggesting a probable exclusive preference for this plant genus as pollen source..
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="355" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1072,1422]" box="[199,514,1181,1206]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,389,1181,1206]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">Nesting biology.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1072,1422]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1216,1241]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">Notes.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Peters" box="[280,431,1217,1241]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" refString="Peters, D. S. (1974) Uber die Untergattung Haetosmia Popov, 1952 (Insecta: Hymenoptera: Megachilidae: Osmia). Senckenbergiana Biologica, 55, 293 - 309." type="journal article" year="1974">Peters (1974)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Müller &amp; Griswold" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[568,670,1216,1241]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="altera">
<emphasis box="[568,670,1216,1241]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">H. altera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Morawitz 1875)" authorityName="Morawitz" authorityYear="1875" baseAuthorityName="Morawitz" baseAuthorityYear="1875" box="[920,1274,1216,1241]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Osmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachyura">
<emphasis box="[920,1072,1216,1241]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">H. brachyura</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Morawitz" box="[1087,1265,1216,1241]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" refString="Morawitz, F. (1875) Bees (Mellifera) I. Apidae genuinae. In: Travel to Turkestan by A. P. Fedtschenko. Moscow, 160 pp." type="book" year="1875">Morawitz 1875</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. However, the distribution areas of the two taxa, which distinctly differ morphologically e.g. in the length of the vertex and the relative length of the second segment of the labial palpus, partly overlap in the Karakum Desert in 
<collectingCountry box="[1274,1432,1288,1313]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
. Therefore, we consider the subspecies 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1974" box="[589,816,1325,1350]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Osmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="brachyura" subSpecies="altera">
<emphasis box="[589,816,1325,1350]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">H. brachyura altera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a species of its own, i.e. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Peters 1974)" authorityName="Müller &amp; Griswold" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[1168,1431,1325,1350]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="altera" status="stat. nov">
<emphasis box="[1168,1270,1325,1350]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">H. altera</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Peters" box="[1285,1423,1325,1349]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" refString="Peters, D. S. (1974) Uber die Untergattung Haetosmia Popov, 1952 (Insecta: Hymenoptera: Megachilidae: Osmia). Senckenbergiana Biologica, 55, 293 - 309." type="journal article" year="1974">Peters 1974</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,248,1361,1384]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">stat. nov</taxonomicNameLabel>
.. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Müller &amp; Griswold" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[267,369,1360,1385]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Haetosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="altera">
<emphasis box="[267,369,1360,1385]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">H. altera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a distinctly larger distribution area than 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Morawitz" baseAuthorityYear="1875" box="[876,1027,1360,1385]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Osmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachyura">
<emphasis box="[876,1027,1360,1385]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">H. brachyura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which seems to be restricted to the Karakum and Kyzylkum Desert.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
